Heartbleed

Target IP: 54.154.18.66

SSL issues are still lurking in the wild! Can you exploit this web servers OpenSSL?

Exploitation & Flag


Metasploit comes with a scanner to identify if a target is vulnerable to the Heartbleed bug. I used the scanner/ssl/openssl_heartbleed auxiliary module to identify if the target machine is vulnerable to Heartbleed. I only initialised the RHOSTS parameter to point to the target machine.


After running the module, I got a hit. The target machine returned more data than it should so it is vulnerable to the bug. Time to exploit it.


There is a popular Python public exploit for this bug which can be found here. I downloaded this exploit on my machine.


And using the command python2 heartbleed.py 54.154.18.66 -n 100, I ran it against the target machine. I set the n to 100 to increase the number of concurrent connections. However, even a small number of connection works. And bingo! The flag THM{sSl-Is-BaD} is displayed in the picture above highlighted in yellow. GG.
